com.linkly.pos.sdk.service.impl

Class PosApiService

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.linkly.pos.sdk.service.impl.PosApiService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IPosApiService

    public class PosApiService
extends java.lang.Object
implements IPosApiService
    POS API service for communicating with the Cloud POS API v2. This service adopts an event-driven architecture to facilitate asynchronous communication with the API. Requests will be sent to the API in a thread and the result returned via the corresponding IPosApiEventListener method. The user of this service must provided an implementation of IPosApiEventListener which handles all the methods accordingly. To use this service the PIN pad must first be paired using PairingRequest or if the PIN pad was previously paired use setPairSecret(String) to set the pairing secret.

      • pairingRequest

        public void pairingRequest(PairingRequest request)
        Pair with the PIN pad. Pairing only needs to occur once and must occur before any requests can be sent to the PIN pad. Upon successful pairing the IPosApiEventListener.pairingComplete(PairingRequest, com.linkly.pos.sdk.models.authentication.PairingResponse) listener will be invoked. PairingResponse.getSecret() should be stored securely by the client. In cases where the PosApiService is initialised and the pair secret is known, it should be passed to the service using setPairSecret(String) to avoid unnecessary re-pairing. Implementation of pairing with the PIN pad.
        Specified by:
        pairingRequest in interface IPosApiService
        Parameters:
        request - Pairing request.
